# Phase 2 Lambda runtime dependencies — direct pins.
# Generate requirements.txt via:
#   .venv/bin/pip-compile --resolver=backtracking --output-file=requirements.txt requirements.in
#
# Direct pins are exact; transitive deps (e.g. networkx via yake) are
# resolved by pip-compile and locked into requirements.txt.
#
# Why the PyTorch CPU index: AWS Lambda has no GPU. The default torch
# wheel from PyPI bundles ~2.8 GB of NVIDIA CUDA libs (cuBLAS, cuDNN,
# cuSPARSE, cuFFT, etc.) and ~600 MB of Triton — entirely dead weight
# on Lambda's CPU runtime. The PyTorch CPU index serves the same
# version (2.11.0+cpu) without the CUDA payload, cutting the deps
# stage from ~3.1 GB to ~400 MB. PEP 440 makes 2.11.0+cpu sort above
# 2.11.0 with the same constraint string.
#
# transformers==5.8.0 is the Phase 2 candidate; auto-fallback to 5.7.0
# if the deps-only or slow smoke gates fail (per docs/phase2-backend.md).
# huggingface_hub is pinned directly because Hub 1.x renamed/removed
# parameters used by snapshot_download (e.g. local_dir_use_symlinks).

--extra-index-url https://download.pytorch.org/whl/cpu

transformers==5.8.0
torch==2.11.0
yake==0.7.3
huggingface_hub==1.13.0
